============================================================
REFINED: WHAT IS THE MINIMAL QUOTIENT?
============================================================

The star elements are ALL TTs with a fixed first vertex.
So "all star generators" = ALL TT boundaries (every TT is in some star).
That means the generators span ALL of B₁, giving dim(R) = 0.

This is too strong — we need a SUBSET of star constraints.
Let me check: what if we use ONLY the HP-consecutive TTs?


--- n=5: HP-consecutive TTs only ---
  Tested: 720
  dim(R) with HP-TTs only: {3: 240, 4: 374, 5: 100, 6: 6}

--- n=6: HP-consecutive TTs only ---
  Tested: 500
  dim(R) with HP-TTs only: {6: 164, 7: 257, 8: 79}

--- Coboundaries as generators ---

--- n=5 ---
  Tested: 720
  dim(B₁ / (B₁∩im(δ))) = dim R: {6: 720}
  (This is B₁ modulo its intersection with coboundaries)

--- n=6 ---
  Tested: 500
  dim(B₁ / (B₁∩im(δ))) = dim R: {10: 500}
  (This is B₁ modulo its intersection with coboundaries)
